cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and summarization. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a fully data-driven approach to abstractive sentence summarization. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed model is trained end-to-end and scales to a large amount of training data. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as summarization is a common task in information retrieval. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the proposed model is a neural attention-based model.
